(380, 'Heads up note 2025-10-17T22:08:00.000+05:30 from @Rahul Mathur: Hi team, Sharing the heads-up note for our investment in [Quivly](https://www.quivly.ai/). This is an AI-powered platform for usage-based revenue teams - lets you connect all your event signals, predict usage and credit burn, and automate the life cycle of billing. You can think of Quivly as “[Clari](https://www.clari.com/) for Post-Sales teams at usage based billing companies” DeVC is investing $150K as part of a $500K SAFE round @ $15M post money valuation (standard US SAFE terms) *Note: Aakash had to push hard across two meetings, including one in-person in SF in September, to secure this allocation in the round which was already closed. We were able to secure this allocation due to inputs from Chetan (CoFo @ Confido Health) given they overlapped at BITS.* Similar to Hexo & Revenoid - we’’ll do further work during our November ‘25 trip on customer introductions, thesis chats and bringing more Angels to the cap table. **Founders** 1. [Chandrika Maheshwari](https://www.linkedin.com/in/chandrikamaheshwari/) - CEO 1. BITS (2007 to 2011) and MIT Sloan MBA ‘18 1. Post MBA - 2 YOE @ DocuSign and 1.5 YOE @ Plaid 1. 1.5 YOE as CoFo @ Pull (US consumer lending FinTech) 1. 2 YOE @ Google as PMM 1. 4 YOE @ Bain (4 promotions from Analyst to Senior Associate) 1. [Tanay Agarwal](https://www.linkedin.com/in/tanayagrawal19/) – CTO 1. Manipal (2012 to 2016) 1. 4 YOE @ Atlan as Founding Engineer 1. 3.5 YOE @ JP Morgan in Paymen...'),
(381, 'Founders and Key Team: Name – Title - Partha Prittam Nayak — CEO — Ex-Swiggy, Supr Daily, Nestaway; Led Operations & Growth; IIM Bangalore, NIT Rourkela; Focus: company strategy, operations and scale. - Rishabh Gupta — CPTO — Ex-Zepto, Equal, Navi; Built products for scale; IIT Bombay; Focus: product & technology leadership. Relevance of prior experience to problem being solved - Founding team combines growth/ops (delivery/assistance platforms) and scale-product experience, aligned with rapid expansion, SOP-driven execution, and tech-enabled operations.
Product and Technology: Product stage - Pilot / limited market test ongoing; no GA launch yet. Core functionality & tech stack - On-demand trained cooks with ingredient kits; centralized Mother Hub for kit creation; Dark Stores for inventory and fulfillment; Chef app for real-time guidance; barcode-based sourcing history; CV-based color/portion audits; time-tracking and real-time feedback. Unique IP - Kit-based standardization (pre-measured, vacuum-sealed ingredients) enabling high consistency; digital SOPs executed by cooks; barcode-tracing of ingredients; “Kit Moat” as a backbone for scale. Key differentiators vs substitutes - Faster, consistent home meals (40 minutes) with trained cooks; no grocery shopping; high hygiene trust; real-time adjustments (oil/salt/spices); strong emphasis on standardization and safety vs home-cook variability or pure restaurant delivery. Implementation complexity / switching costs - [Inference] ...'),
(383, 'Meeting during Nov ‘25 SF trip: Unfortunately I did not take any notes from this conversation. But putting a raw brain dump here of my chat with Rahul Tarak: 1. Currently part of the team at Composio. 1. Did SPC to mainly explore various spaces but decided to not build a company. 1. Not a backable founder, more of a deep thinker and great L1 candidate which I see playing out at Composio. 1. May end up starting up again in the next 18-24 months. 1. Great node for us to keep in SF to interact with the Desi community and invite to events.'),
(384, 'Heads up note from @Rahul Mathur 2025-11-05T11:13:00.000+05:30: Hi team, Sharing the heads-up note for our investment in [Rakshan AI](https://rakshan.ai/) - It provides audit-ready AI visibility & runtime guardrails (within 30 days of deployment); it is essentially a single graph across code, cloud infra & traffic. DeVC is investing $200K as part of a $1.5M SAFE round @ $15M post money valuation (Post-money cap plus an MFN clause for DeVC) **Founders** 1. [Jayesh Ahire](https://www.linkedin.com/in/jayesh-ahire/) (CEO) 1. 6 YOE @ Traceable AI as founding engineer 1. MS in CS from Stanford Univ 1. BRCs from Naresh and Jyoti (Traceable AI Founders) 1. *++ "Would back him blindly”* 1. *++ "Top product leader at traceable. Depth in ML is outstanding."* 1. [Prashanth HN](https://www.linkedin.com/in/hnprashanth/?originalSubdomain=in) (CTO) 1. 6 YOE @ AntStack as CoFo 1. 15+ years building scalable cloud-native security/engineering teams and startups **Investing Process** 1. Cash has been tracking Jayesh for ~1 year now based on his conversations with Traceable AI founders 1. Summary of views from the meeting: 1. Cash 1. *++ Strong founder and stack ranks well - “Anu from Skydda is in a different league but compared to Aurva and StepSecurity, he’s better"* 1. *++ domain and GTM compounding - seeing this* 1. *++ Has a good rolodex and converting this* 1. *++ Outstanding refs from Jyoti and others in Traceable* 1. RA 1. *++ interesting wedge and good problem statement* 1. *++ liked the...'),
